-- Chi-X Australia Trading Volume Market Share at Record
-- B y   A d a m   H a i g h
-- 2012-09-14T00:00:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-14/chi-x-australia-trading-volume-market-share-at-record.html
Chi-X Australia Pty., rival to
Australia’s operator of the country’s largest stock exchange  ASX
Ltd. (ASX) , posted a record 7.2 percent of market share for equity
trading yesterday, according to its data.  That accounts for about A$214 million ($225 million) of
share trading, the data show. ASX lost its monopoly as
Australia’s only public venue in November last year with the
entry of Chi- X, backed by Nomura Holdings Inc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Adam Haigh in Sydney at 
